HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 640
By Vital
A RESOLUTION to honor the Chattanooga Mocs men's basketball
team on winning the 2025 National Invitation
Tournament.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that this General Assembly should salute those student athletes
who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as true champions of
whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such exemplary group of young men is the Mocs basketball team of the
University of Tennessee at Chattanooga (UTC or Chattanooga), whose members have proven
themselves to be the fiercest of competitors and truly worthy of admiration by winning the 2025
National Invitation Tournament (NIT), a victory that made history; and
WHEREAS, the 2025 NIT crown is UTC's first NCAA-sanctioned tournament title in its
Division I history, as well as the first such title won by any Southern Conference (SoCon)
program in the conference's 105-year history; and
WHEREAS, Chattanooga also matched a school record for total wins, finishing with a
29-9 overall record; the Mocs closed out the 2024-2025 season on a tremendous hot streak,
winning seventeen of their final eighteen games; and
WHEREAS, after winning the SoCon regular season championship with a 15-3 record,
Chattanooga fell in the semifinals of the SoCon tournament for their final loss of the season; and
WHEREAS, determined to get revenge for that loss, UTC entered the NIT with a
determined outlook and a chip on their shoulders and proceeded to win five straight games; and
WHEREAS, the Mocs defeated Middle Tennessee State 109-103 in a triple overtime
thriller and then knocked off Dayton 87-72 in the second round; and
